The Blooming Lotus Yoga Retreat in Bali is an oasis of peace and tranquility. Firmly rooted in the classical yoga tradition we offer one of the most in-depth yoga teacher training Bali has to offer. Our 200 hr. yoga teacher training certification courses (YTT) in Ubud are Yoga Alliance registered, allowing students to teach yoga worldwide. We also offer Bali yoga retreats that are perfect for both beginner and intermediate students who wish to deepen their practice while exploring the beauty of Bali and its spiritual culture. Our silent meditation retreats teach a complete technique of meditation that focuses on the ultimate aim of yoga: Self-Realization. Join us in paradise for an unforgettable immersion into the essence of yoga.

I recently attended a yoga retreat at Blooming Lotus Yoga in Ubud, and while the experience was overall beautiful, there are a few things to consider before booking.

The accommodation was absolutely stunning—serene surroundings, a private pool, and a peaceful atmosphere that made it the perfect place to unwind. The food was another highlight, with two delicious, nourishing meals a day that truly complemented the retreat experience. The service and stuff there deserve 5* as well.

However, I specifically chose a yoga retreat with daily Vinyasa, expecting a dynamic practice, but the schedule was heavily focused on meditation and theory. While reviewing fundamental knowledge is always valuable, it’s not necessarily what you want on a dream yoga getaway—especially if you're looking for more movement and flow. The retreat calendar only lists one general program, Yoga Bliss Retreat, so be aware that the actual content may lean more towards mindfulness and beginner-friendly teachings rather than active practice.

If you're looking for a deeply introspective and meditative retreat, this might be perfect for you. But if you’re after a more dynamic yoga experience, I’d recommend checking the schedule carefully or confirming details in advance.

Thank you for your great review Petra! We're so happy to hear that you enjoyed the serene accommodations, nourishing meals, and our dedicated staff - we strive to create a peaceful and supportive retreat for all our guests.  

Our retreats are consciously designed to offer a holistic approach, blending yoga asana, meditation, and self-inquiry to create a truly authentic yoga experience beyond what is typically found in fitness orientated yoga classes . While we do include dynamic movement, we also place a strong emphasis on mindfulness, reflection and inner growth, which many of our guests find deeply rewarding and far beyond the scope of most yoga studio classes. 

We appreciate your feedback and hope to welcome you back for another beautiful experience!

I’ve just finished up a 23 day Bali Yoga Teacher Training at Blooming Lotus. The training is held at the beautiful Ubud 88 Villas just on the outskirts of Ubud. It has beautiful views of the jungle and the staff could not be any more lovely! The vegan food is delicious and changes daily. It’s mostly organic and locally sourced.
The course itself is intensive but broken up with 3.5 days off spread over the 23 days. The group was fairly small and everyone was great, coming from different places from around the globe.
Lily and Mandy who teach the majority of the classes are both extremely knowledgeable and I have learnt so much about the history of yoga and also about my own spiritual journey.
Lily is particular is amazing!
If you’re wanting to just learn the mechanics of teaching yoga though, then this training isn’t for you. Be ready to meditate for up to 2 hours per day and get in touch with the challenging parts of yourself as you learn about things such as Karma and many other aspects of spirituality. 🙏

It’s wonderful that the teachings resonated with you, and that you embraced the spiritual depth of the program. Your kind words about the staff, food, and setting mean a lot to us! Wishing you all the best on your yoga journey—may it continue to unfold beautifully. 🙏✨

Blooming Lotus Yoga is truly an amazing experience. This was my first time attending a retreat/ yoga and meditation classes and it exceeded all my expectations.

From start to finish the service and staff are attentive and welcoming. I was really nervous attending alone but I instantly felt at home, I had a shared room and instantly made friends with my roomie. The villas are beautiful, with a private pool, sun loungers, kitchen and living room.

The yoga teachers are all truely amazing at what they do, introducing us to the world of meditation and yoga practice. They give you  options within movements so all fitness/yoga levels can feel comfortable. We practice a variety of meditation and yoga techniques with a focus on relaxation, mindfulness and sense of self (whilst still getting your body moving). If you are looking for a purely fitness yoga this is not for you, but what you’ll get is a sense of calm and knowledge of your own mind and body.

Each session begins with a meditation and breathing exercise before moving onto yoga practice. The practice is a range of vinyasa, yin, asana, pranayama etc and teachers are open to suggestions within what style you would like to practice. They encourage you to speak to them after class with any questions and are always kind and happy.

The food was great, with a different breakfast and dinner each day. I really enjoyed the food (especially the tacos) and the free tea and coffee is available throughout the day. I always left feeling nourished and full of goodness.

I also took advantage of the spa on site and had a wonderful holistic massage (you must try it)

If you’re thinking about doing a yoga and meditation retreat this is definitely the place to go. I would recommend this to everyone!

Thank you so much guys 🌸🥰

As a couple we have just completed the most amazing Bali yoga teacher training at Blooming Lotus Yoga in Ubud.  Ubud Corner, the location of Blooming Lotus, is a short drive away from the noise and traffic of Ubud, it is set in the most incredible peaceful surroundings overlooking the Balinese jungle with views over the river to a nearby temple. Our villa was of the highest standard, with a private pool, a super king-sized bed and was kept beautifully clean. The staff at Ubud Corner 88 are gentle and sweet and cannot do enough for you. We chose Booming Lotus for our 200-hour YTT course as we wished to deepen our understanding of the spiritual roots of yoga and explore meditation and pranayama, as well as improving our asana practice. Blooming Lotus excelled at every level. The teaching manuals were of the highest quality the daily lectures were fantastic, and all the teachers were of the highest possible standard delivering teaching and coaching in a gentle and supportive manner. We began and ended the day with meditation practice and the remainder of the day was spent learning about the art of mantra, the spiritual roots of yoga and teaching practice.  The practical exercises were thoughtfully constructed and well-paced and through a careful process of layering we progressed from teaching a short sequence to ultimately being capable of delivering a 60-minute flow class. We met some wonderful people on the course, made many friends from all over the world and the course caters well to all levels ages and aptitudes. Thank you Mandy and Lily for an unforgettable three weeks!

It’s wonderful that you found the setting, teachings, and supportive environment so enriching, and we’re delighted that you and Caroline felt guided and nurtured throughout your journey. Mandy, Lily, and the entire team will be so grateful to know their dedication made such a lasting impact. Wishing you both endless joy and growth on your yoga path—hope to see you again in the future! 🙏✨

Blooming Lotus was an amazing experience. The location is breathtaking, the highlight being the infinity pools in each villa. The villas were super spacious with the most comfortable beds during my trip.

There was a really special vibe, very calm and surrounded by nature. The staff was exceptionally friendly. Yoga classes were taught by local teachers - big plus for me! It was great to learn about cultural and spiritual aspects of their Yoga practice. The classes were varied, with more active sessions, lots of meditation and quieter practices. I feel the teachers could have aligned a bit better, some stuff was talked about several times while other parts felt a bit left out.

As the location is a bit remote, it is a bit tricky to get grab/gojek drivers to find you but always worked out in the end. In ~15 minutes you can reach massage places or cafés and the villa offers free transfers to Ubud every second day.

The only downside for me was the food, which of course is subjective. For me, it tasted very bland and e.g. for breakfast, after two hours of yoga, 2 pieces of bread with jam is a bit little. I understand they follow a certain concept but I believe it could still be healthy but a bit tastier. We ordered room service once, there the food was much better than the included one and another participant mentioned she liked the food better on a previous visit. I would come back anytime if food would be elevated a little.

This place is really special and a great choice for people seeking a true retreat.

Thank you so much for your wonderful review Nina! We’re delighted to hear that you had an amazing experience and that you loved the location and the peaceful atmosphere. It’s wonderful to know that you enjoyed the yoga classes and appreciated the cultural and spiritual aspects shared by our teachers. We also appreciate your comments on the food and will share them with our team as we continuously strive to improve. We’d love to welcome you back and hope to offer an even more enjoyable retreat next time! ✨

My Bali yoga teacher training at Blooming Lotus yoga was an amazing experience. It is so much more than just at YTT- its a course in self-knowledge, spiritual education, personal transformation and creating community. The team at BLY are true yogis that walk the walk, both kowledgeable and compassionate, and truly devoted to their students (when I got sick during my YTT my teacher came over to my off-site hotel on her day off to bring me medicine and make sure I was taken care of). BLY is a family that will support you all the way through your YTT and beyond, they deeply care about creating a strong and close-knit community- there are so many follow-on activities to keep you connected, from monthly digital meditation sessions to a chance to come back entirely free of charge to repeat your training and find something new in it. I loved my time at BLY, I loved the group of people I was with, my teachers, and the beautiful serene location. If you are serious about the actual path of yoga, not simply fitnessing in pretzel poses, I could not think of a better training to set you on your way.
